===Etymology===
From {{ME.}} < {{ML.}} '''[[instrumentalis]]''' < '''[[instruere]]''' ("to build into, set up, construct, furnish," hence "to train") < '''[[in-]]''' ("on") + '''[[struere]]''' ("to put together, arrange, pile up, build, construct") < Proto-Indo-European '''[[Wiktionary Appendix:Proto-Indo-European roots|*streu-]]''' ("to spread, extend, stretch out").

